overview: The user initiated a request for a comprehensive review of their sleep
  questionnaire application, comparing its current implementation against a
  detailed Statement of Work and a questionnaire specification. Following the
  review, the agent identified several missing features and proposed a detailed
  plan for their implementation. The agent then proceeded to implement these
  features, including a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness with critical safety
  messaging, detection and tailored recommendations for COMISA and Insufficient
  Sleep Syndrome, the addition of a "Resources & Next Steps" section with
  external links in both the web and PDF reports, a weighted scoring system for
  Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS), an expanded CSV export to include all
  questionnaire data, and new questions for pain severity and chronic fatigue
  screening with integrated report logic. The implementation involved updating
  data types, validation schemas, UI components, and report generation logic
  across multiple files to ensure full functionality and adherence to the
  specified criteria.
